text: Marie-Paule Blé (born 6 July 1998) is a French taekwondo practitioner. She won a bronze medal in middleweight at the 2019 World Taekwondo Championships, after being defeated by Lee Da-bin in the semifinal. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1998 births Category:Living people Category:French female taekwondo practitioners Category:Medalists at the 2019 Summer Universiade Category:Universiade medalists in taekwondo Category:Universiade bronze medalists for France Category:World Taekwondo Championships medalists
